    Mustard Chicken and Mash Recipe<= /h2>
    =20
    25 May 2016 =20
    =20 =20

    Serves 4

    Ingredients

    8= chicken thighs

    Oil for frying

    50g butter

    1 onion, sliced

    1 tbs smoked paprika

    20g wholegrain mustar= d

    300ml strong chicken stock

    150g green beans

    1 tsp sugar

    200g sour cream

    12 small gherkins, sliced<= /p>

    1 tbs capers

    1 tbs choppe= d parsley

    1 tbs chopped tarragon

    1 tbs chopped mint

    250g dry mashed potato<= /p>

    80g butter

    Method

    1. = Fry the chicken for 4 minutes to crisp up the skin and then remove.

    2. Gently fry the onion in butter for 5 minutes, scraping= all the chicken bits.

    3. Add the mustard and papr= ika, cook 3 minutes, add the chicken, stock and bring to boil.

    4. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes to cook the chicken.

    5. Add everything else, except the herbs, and cook for = 5 minutes.

    6. Add the herbs.

    7. Beat the butter into the hot mash and serve with the chicken.

    = This recipe will be available for 6 months from the date of publication= .
